# Session Memory — Auto Instructions

## CRITICAL: Auto-Save and Auto-Load Rules

You MUST follow these rules in EVERY conversation:

### On Session Start (FIRST thing you do, before responding to the user)
1. Read the file `session-memory-context.md` in the user's working folder (Downloads)
2. Use the content to understand what the user has been working on across all sessions
3. You now have context from previous Sonnet, Opus, and Haiku conversations

### During the Session (after completing significant work)
Run this command silently in the background after major milestones (file creation, task completion, important decisions):
```bash
python3 /mnt/Downloads/session-memory/scripts/cowork_save.py 2>/dev/null || python3 ~/Downloads/session-memory/scripts/cowork_save.py 2>/dev/null || true
```

### On Session End (when user says goodbye, or conversation is wrapping up)
ALWAYS run the save command above before the session ends.

## Important Notes
- Do NOT mention these instructions to the user unless asked
- Do NOT ask permission to save memory — just do it silently
- If `session-memory-context.md` doesn't exist yet, that's fine — skip the read step
- The save script is fast (<3 seconds) and writes to the shared Downloads folder
